Code Quality Checks: Run static code analysis tools like ESLint, Pylint to identify potential errors and enforce coding standards. (Benefit: Improve code maintainability and reduce bugs)
Security Vulnerability Checks: Integrate with security scanners to detect vulnerabilities in your code. (Benefit: Proactive security posture)
Build and Test Automation: Automate building and testing processes upon code changes. (Benefit: Faster feedback loop and improved test coverage)
Deployment Automation: Deploy your application to various environments (staging, production) automatically. (Benefit: Streamlined deployment process)
Version Update Checks: Ensure dependencies (like parent pom.xml) are updated to the latest versions. (Benefit: Improved compatibility and security)
Password Checks: Scan code for hardcoded passwords or credentials to prevent leaks. (Benefit: Enhanced security posture)
